  "doc_id": "46998",
  "text": "Of the five genomic regions (chromosomes 1B, 5A, 5B, 6B, and 7B) identified for SB resistance, 1B, 5B and 7B were mapped previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The genomic region 7B also was detected in a previous study [CITATION_4] . Likewise, one minor QTL with phenotypic variation effect (R 2 ) of 15.1% was detected on chromosome 1B [CITATION_5] and one major QTL, Qsb.bhu-5B, was mapped on chromosome 5B [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . No previous evidence was observed for resistance to SB on chromosome 5A and thus this region appears to be a novel.",
